<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>Court Forms</title>
  <style>
    {{{print_css}}}

    @page {
      size: A4;
      margin: 12mm;
    }

    body {
      margin: 0;
      color: #1f1635;
      font-size: 10pt;
      line-height: 1.55;
    }

    .hero,
    .panel,
    .warning-box,
    .list-card {
      page-break-inside: avoid;
      break-inside: avoid;
    }

    .hero,
    .panel,
    .warning-box,
    .list-card {
      border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;
      background: #fff;
      padding: 1em 1.1em;
      margin-bottom: 0.9em;
    }

    .hero {
      background: #faf8ff;
      border-color: #ddd6fe;
    }

    .eyebrow,
    .chip {
      display: inline-block;
      margin-bottom: 0.45em;
      padding: 0.18em 0.55em;
      border-radius: 0;
      font-size: 8.5pt;
      font-weight: 700;
      letter-spacing: 0.04em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      background: #ede9fe;
      color: #4c1d95;
    }

    h1,
    h2,
    h3 {
      color: #231942;
    }

    h1 {
      margin: 0 0 0.25em 0;
      font-size: 18pt;
    }

    h2 {
      margin: 1.1em 0 0.55em 0;
      font-size: 12pt;
    }

    h3 {
      margin: 0 0 0.35em 0;
      font-size: 10.5pt;
    }

    p {
      margin: 0.3em 0;
    }

    ul {
      margin: 0.4em 0 0 1.1em;
      padding: 0;
    }

    li {
      margin: 0.3em 0;
    }

    .grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
      gap: 0.85em;
    }

    .warning-box {
      background: #fef2f2;
      border-color: #fecaca;
    }

    .muted {
      color: #6b7280;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="hero">
    <div class="eyebrow">{{pack_title}}</div>
    <h1>Court Forms</h1>
    <p><strong>These forms are completed using the same facts, dates, and grounds as your notice and service record.</strong></p>
    <p>{{pack_supporting_line}}</p>
  </div>

  <div class="grid">
    <div class="list-card">
      <div class="chip">Included</div>
      <h3>Form N5</h3>
      <p>The possession claim form that starts the county court claim.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="list-card">
      <div class="chip">Included</div>
      <h3>Form N119</h3>
      <p>The particulars of claim that explain the grounds, timeline, and arrears position relied on in court.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="panel">
    <h2>Do not change</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>grounds</li>
      <li>arrears figures</li>
      <li>dates</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="warning-box">
    <h2>Alignment warning</h2>
    <p>Inconsistency between the served notice and the claim is one of the most common reasons possession cases are delayed or challenged.</p>
    <p class="muted">Keep the Section 8 notice, N215, arrears schedule, Form N5, and Form N119 reading from the same timeline and figures.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="panel">
    <h2>Next step</h2>
    <p>Review the claim forms against the served notice and issue them only when the notice timeline allows proceedings.</p>
  </div>
</body>
</html>
